---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Us" description="Learn about the mission and vision behind SiteIntelica">
  <div class="container prose">
    <h1>About SiteIntelica</h1>
    <p>
      In the high-stakes world of digital marketing and web development, understanding your competition isn't just an advantage—it's a necessity. SiteIntelica was built to level the playing field by giving you X-Ray vision into any website on the internet.
    </p>

    <h2>Our Mission</h2>
    <p>
      We believe in transparency on the web. Our mission is to democratize technology intelligence, making it possible for independent developers, founders, and marketers to see exactly what software, frameworks, and ad networks are driving the success of industry leaders.
    </p>

    <h2>How the "Spy" Engine Works</h2>
    <p>
      Behind the scenes, SiteIntelica leverages an advanced, server-side Node.js scraping engine powered by Wappalyzer Core. Features include:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Deep DOM Analysis:</strong> We don't just check headers. Our engine parses the entire HTML tree looking for tell-tale CSS classes and JavaScript objects that reveal frontend frameworks like React, Vue, and Astro.</li>
      <li><strong>Marketing Pixel Detection:</strong> See exactly which remarketing and analytics platforms (like Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel, or Hotjar) a competitor is using.</li>
      <li><strong>Infrastructure Mapping:</strong> Discover the bare-metal CDNs, web servers (Nginx, Apache), and cloud providers (AWS, Vercel, Netlify) hosting the application.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Built for the Modern Web</h2>
    <p>
      SiteIntelica itself is a testament to cutting-edge web architecture, built entirely on <strong>Astro</strong> with server-rendered API endpoints for maximum speed, SEO optimization, and an unmatched user experience.
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
